A '''borganism''' is an organization of autonomous [[organism]]s that exhibit [[collectivism]]: individual "units" that have merged to yield a unified construct.  Such an amalgam may possess a [[collective consciousness]], arguably an [[emergence|emergent phenomenon]] of [[social network]]ing.

The word and concept are derived from [[Borg (fictional aliens)|the Borg]], a race of [[cyborg]]s in the fictional [[Star Trek]] universe with a [[hive mind]] that operates as one.

In [[biology]], such an organization, for example a bee hive, is usually called a [[superorganism]].

Among [[anarchocapitalism|anarchocapitalist]] and [[transhumanism|transhuman]] [[libertarianism|libertarians]], the government is often seen as a proto-borganism, especially governments like that of the [[Soviet Union]].

